Sales at major South Korean
department stores gained the most in eight months in December as
consumers stepped up shopping in the holiday season.  Outlays (KODSDEPT)  at the three biggest chains rose 11 percent from a
year earlier after a 0.5 percent fall in November, the Ministry
of  Knowledge Economy  said in a statement today.  Discount-store
sales (KODSDISC)  increased 3.7 percent, todayâ€™s report showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
